article.description: SE Missouri soars past Central Baptist 118-56
article.headline: SE Missouri soars past Central Baptist 118-56
article.linkText: SE Missouri soars past Central Baptist 118-56
article.story: CAPE GIRARDEAU, Mo. -- Jarekious Bradley had 21 points on Monday night to lead six teammates in double figures in Southeast Missouri's 118-56 blowout of Central Baptist. The Redhawks (1-1) were 17 of 35 from 3-point range. Bradley was 3 of 6 from the arc and needed only 23 minutes to notch his second 20-point game this season. C.J. Reese had 15 points and eight assists and Lucas Nutt added nine points and nine assists. SE Missouri built a 22-point lead at the half before hitting 12 of 17 3-pointers during a 69-29 second-half run. The Redhawks controlled the action on both ends of the floor, edging Central Baptist 27-6 in assists and 15-5 in steals. Kevin Daniels had 16 points and Terrell Eskridge added 12 for Central Baptist.
